subject: p18517718
Findings: In comparison with study of earlier in this date, the tip of the endotracheal tube measures approximately 46 cm above the carina. Nasogastric tube extends into the stomach, with the tip crossing the lower margin of the image. Increased opacification is seen at the right base medially. It is unclear whether this represents crowding of pulmonary vessels, atelectasis, or, in the appropriate clinical setting, a developing consolidation.
